<AbstractNarration>0097124 -- Smyth/OSU&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;This project is a preliminary numerical investigation of whether Holmboe &lt;br/&gt;waves can generate appreciable mixing in idealized stratified flow &lt;br/&gt;configurations similar to those that might be expected in some oceanic &lt;br/&gt;regimes such as exchange flows.  This research will examine whether a &lt;br/&gt;significant mixing efficiency can be achieved.  A spectral model of a&lt;br/&gt;continuously stratified flow containing a sharp density gradient and a &lt;br/&gt;more gentle shear gradient will be used to make direct numerical&lt;br/&gt;simulations of the growth and nonlinear development of Holmboe waves.&lt;br/&gt;If numerical results provide evidence that the Holmboe instability leads&lt;br/&gt;to effective mixing, this will provide an impetus for a more thorough &lt;br/&gt;investigation of the life-cycle of Holmboe instabilities and the &lt;br/&gt;associated mixing. &lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
